description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Therapy Assistants to work at Scunthorpe General Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In this post you will work as part of the team that provide physiotherapy rehabilitation for patients on the acute medical wards and emergency care centre as part of the therapy team..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The candidate must have good communication and interpersonal skills. You will be expected to be involved in supporting the therapists with treament programmes, data collection, ordering equipment and accompanying therapists on home visits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide in-service training, CPD and appraisal. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is permanent and may suit someone who is already experienced in this area of rehabilitation or someone who is looking to start a career in the NHS.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will provide assistance to Therapy staff in organising and delivering efficient, effective patient care. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This will include carrying out delegated clinical work with patients, administrative and clerical duties within the service area. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post is for 30 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Logan, Operational Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mandy.logan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07736486385&lt;/p&gt;
